Reasoning: The paper deals with feature tracking in video, which is a common problem in computer vision. The use of a joint tracking framework and the ability to handle both rigid and non-rigid motions suggest that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of machine learning techniques to improve tracking results, which could place it in the machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the mention of real-time performance suggests that the paper could also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
